review_blob: 2003 Vintage, one of the best beers I have ever tasted.  Aroma was intense but inviting, raisin, and malty.  Carmel, mild fruit and scotch all come through a nice strong head.
This is one of the best Oktoberfest beers I have had in a long time.  Color was bright amber, creamy head, strong malt character and hints of spice.  Very drinkable.
